武汉一家七口抗疫｜“像我的情况那么糟糕，也开始好转了”。
Seven mouths of wuhan plague, "As bad as I am, it's beginning to get better."
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
武汉市青山区市民 夏女士澎湃新闻记者 薛莎莎 整理夏女士家住武汉市青山区，家中七口人：公婆、父母、丈夫、她和三岁大的孩子。
Ms. Xue Sha Sha, a journalist from Qingshan District, Wuhan City, lives in the Qingshan area of Wuhan City. There are seven members of her family: her mother-in-law, her parents, her husband, her three-year-old child.
此前，澎湃新闻曾报道了她一家七口疑似感染新冠肺炎的故事。
Earlier, Peng Pai News had reported the story of seven members of her family suspected of contracting New Crown Pneumonia.
她公婆、丈夫先后查出肺部感染或病变，住进了武汉市第九医院的隔离病房。
Her mother-in-law, her husband has detected lung infection or pathological changes, live in Wuhan City Ninth Hospital isolation ward.
她父母肺部也感染，此前在武汉市中心医院治疗。
Her parents, whose lungs were also infected, had been treated at Wuhan Central Hospital.
随后，公婆、丈夫和母亲所做的新冠病毒核酸检测，均呈阳性。
Subsequently, the mother-in-law, husband and mother-in-law tested positive for the new crown virus nucleic acid.
夏女士10日做的CT检查报告显示，“复查有好转趋势”。
Ms. Xia did the CT examination report on the 10th, "review has an improvement trend."
2月4日上午，年逾六旬的父亲在住院治疗期间“突发重症”抢救无效离世，她和家人未能见到父亲最后一面。
On the morning of February 4, her father, who was over 60, died of an "acute medical condition" while hospitalized. She and her family were unable to see her father for the last time.
1月底，夏女士查出肺部已感染。
At the end of January, Ms. Xia detected a lung infection.
2月4日，她在武汉市中心医院等来一个床位，随后入院治疗。
On 4 February, she was admitted to hospital after waiting for a bed at Wuhan Central Hospital.
2月12日，夏女士称，她此前做的两次核酸检测结果已出，一次阳性，一次阴性。
On 12 February, Ms. Xia stated that her previous two nucleic acid tests had yielded positive results, one positive and one negative.
她老公和三岁孩子的最新检测结果都是阳性，仍需要继续住院治疗。
Her husband and three-year-old children have recently tested positive and still need to be hospitalized.
夏女士今天胃口很好，午饭和晚饭各吃了两份盒饭。
Ms. Xia has a very good appetite today. She had two boxed lunches and two lunches for dinner.
她心态挺好，认为事情既然发生了，就要去面对。
She was in a good mood and thought that since it had happened, she would have to face it.
现在康复出院的人越来越多，她也看到了希望。
More and more people were recovering and leaving the hospital, and she saw hope.
午饭和晚饭，夏女士各吃了两份盒饭。
For lunch and dinner, Ms. Xia ate two boxes of rice each.
本文图片均由夏女士供图澎湃新闻将持续以日记的形式，记录夏女士一家在治疗期间所经历的种种。
This article by Ms. Xia Tu Peng news will continue to keep a diary of the Ms. Xia family experience during the treatment.
以下是夏女士的日记：2月12日 星期三 晴今天是我入院的第九天，每天都要进行常规的治疗。
The following is Ms. Xia's diary: February 12 Wednesday Fine Today is my ninth day on the hospital and I need regular treatment every day.
昨天检查显示我的肝功能有点异常，医生为我加了护肝的药物。
Yesterday's exam showed that my liver function was a little abnormal. The doctor gave me some liver care medicine.
今天，我的身体各项指征还比较平稳，应该进入平稳期了，希望快点进入好转期。
Today, my body indicators are relatively stable, should enter a period of stability, hope to enter a period of improvement as soon as possible.
近期，我的胃口比较好，感觉医院的盒饭已经填不饱我的胃了。
Recently, my appetite is better, I feel the hospital lunch box has not filled my stomach.
如果护士有多的盒饭，我就再要一份。
If the nurse has more boxed rice, I'll have another one.
午饭和晚饭，我都吃了两份盒饭。
For lunch and dinner, I ate two boxed meals.
这个病很消耗身体。
The disease consumes the body.
以前健康的时候，我天天想着减肥也没见掉二两肉，现在一日三餐一顿不落地吃，还吃水果，我竟然瘦了。
Before healthy time, I thought of losing weight every day did not see two or two meat, now three meals a day do not fall to the ground eat fruit, I even lost weight.
唯一不好的就是，我不太能睡得着，特别是白天，精神明显跟不上了还是睡不着。
The only bad thing is that I can't sleep well, especially during the day, when I can't keep up or sleep.
我想了办法，戴上耳机眼罩听轻音乐闭目养神。
I figured out how to put on earphone blindfolds and listen to light music.
多睡会觉的话，身体应该恢复得快一点。
If you sleep more, you should recover more quickly.
今天医生说，我7日做的核酸检测结果是阳性，10日是阴性。
Today, my doctor said that I tested positive for nucleic acid on the 7th and negative on the 10th.
老公和孩子最新的检测结果都是阳性，他们也还要继续住院治疗。
Husband and child's latest test results are positive, they also continue to be hospitalized.
今天一位感染新冠肺炎已康复出院的朋友跟我说，她在家隔离得快抑郁了。
Today, a friend who had recovered from pneumonia told me that she was in quarantine and was depressed.
住在医院的我，还开导了她，我向她讲了我一家七口的经历。
Living in the hospital, I also enlighten her, I told her about my family of seven experience.
我说，“这都没什么，像我的情况那么糟糕，也开始好转了。
I said, "It's all right, it's just as bad as my situation, and it's starting to get better.
”夏女士开导在家隔离的朋友。
"Ms. Xia instructed her friends, who were isolated at home.
我的内心算是比较强大的，我老公病情严重时，我也常鼓励他。
My heart is more powerful, when my husband is seriously ill, I often encourage him.
没有办法，事情既然发生了，我们就要去面对它。
There was no way. Now that it had happened, we had to face it.
我们的恐慌更多的是对新冠病毒的未知，现在康复出院的病人越来越多，我们也看到了希望。
Our panic is more about the unknown coronavirus, and we are seeing hope as more patients recover and leave the hospital.
2020年2月12日本期编辑邢潭推荐阅读。
Xingtan, editor of the current issue of February 12, 2020.
